  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Brexit and inequality in the UK</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The research will increase our impact and range of our in -house research as this research will be done by the market insights team and shared internally across Campaigns, Policy and Influencing Team (CPIT) and other divisions.  It may also achieve external impact depending on the findings, and this impact can influence positively for our campaigns and policy positions.  This is a new area of work because previously those who voted to leave didn&apos;t exist and were seen as a minority in the country.  It is supporting increased impact of advocacy because we will be able to tailor our messages to reach this target group and to support our ability to shift the popular narratives to be more in favour with Oxfam&apos;s views.  It will increase knowledge and learning and sharing because we will learn more about this group of people and their thoughts on inequality, how to best reach them in terms of messages and practical/programme support, and how to use this messaging to influence decision makers, and so we will also be sharing that knowledge.</narrative>
  </description>
